    "narrative": "The Austin Waves offense is anchored today by **Gunnar Henderson** (81.88), who faces Bello in a favorable park environment that pads his base projection by 16%. Despite a 34% rain risk, **Gunnar Henderson** remains our elite start, benefiting from a high-efficiency dynamic platoon split against the right-hander. Following closely is **Kyle Tucker** (73.75), whose 0.372 xwOBA against Jameson Taillon makes him a core pillar. We are also projecting a strong day for **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** (66.24), who draws a favorable matchup against Williams; while he faces a slight dynamic platoon drag, his top-tier xwOBA and the high-value #3 spot in the order keep him firmly in the 60+ range. **Drake Baldwin** (63.73) and **Andy Pages** (60.68) round out our high-efficiency group, both offering solid counting stat potential against Andrew Painter and Jameson Taillon, respectively.\n\nStrategic considerations for the remaining slots focused heavily on speed and platoon optimization. **Nasim Nunez** (60.13) earns the start over **Brady House** (52.73) specifically for his potential to address our scarcity in stolen bases, despite a minor order-position penalty. The tightest call on the bench was **Coby Mayo** (55.65), who actually boasts a strong park-adjusted projection against Bello. However, we opted to limit **Coby Mayo** due to a lower efficiency score compared to our active hitters and the same 34% rain risk currently threatening **Gunnar Henderson**. Meanwhile, **Heliot Ramos** (58.46) retains his spot in the lineup largely due to Sandy Alcantara\u2019s slow delivery, which provides a latent opportunity for a stolen base, an essential factor given our aggressive pursuit of the SB category. We are continuing to monitor the status of **Liam Hicks**, **Nasim Nunez**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Josh Jung**, **Kyle Tucker**, **Josh Lowe**, **Andy Pages**, and **Heliot Ramos**, all of whom are currently tagged with \"Lineup Pending\" designations; final adjustments will be made if official batting orders shift these players out of their projected spots.",
